document.label: def:divisibility
document.definition: For integers a and b, “a divides b” means there exists an integer d such that b = a·d.

proof_steps.statement: There exists k ∈ ℤ such that n = 12·k.

document.label: thm:div12-3
document.claim: For every integer n, if 12 divides n then 3 divides n.
